            <h2>The Tunnock Prize 2024 Winner</h2>
            <p>The Tunnock Prize for 2024 is awarded to Grant Schreiber, a PhD candidate at the University of Guelph, Canada, for his essay entitled 'Kirk Session Financial Records and the Poor of Aberdeen, 1602-27'. Grant provided a presentation about his research at the AGM of the Scottish Records Association on 17 December, and his winning essay will appear in a forthcoming volume of <a href="https://www.scottishrecordsassociation.org/scottish-archives">Scottish Archives</a>.</p>
